@scottpurdy, I used a simple way to avoid creating another layer of manylinux docker image and the corresponding repository and build system integration resources. I modeled the manylinux scripts on the existing build-linux-release.sh and its debug counterpart that both use `setup-dependencies-linux.sh` to set up the environment and tooling installation/configuration.

Similarly to the use ofsetup-dependencies-linux.sh by the existing linux build scripts, the manylinux build sources manylinux.rc to set up the necessary environment.

I think that it's a reasonable tradeoff that matches and benefits from the existing design pattern.

