@khalibartan Try to avoid defining properties in methods other than `__init__`. It helps in keeping things clear as you will be able to just see the `__init__` method and can tell what are the properties.

So here rather than assigning value to `self.network_name` just simply return `temp[0][0]` and in the `__init__` method rather that simply calling `self.get_network_name()` do something like `self.network_name = self.get_network_name()`. 
The end result is the same in both cases but the second method will make the code much more cleaner.

